# Skill #3 - Version Control

Skill Demonstration Challenge

---

## Objective

Demonstrate that you can setup and use Github

* Create a Github repository
* Setup Github Desktop
* Create a local repository
* Clone your repo onto your computer
* Clone the instructor repo to get sample code


## Demonstration of Skill

These screen shots are proof of skill. 

### Create a Github repository
* Visit [Github.com](https://github.com) and sign up for a free account
* Create a repo
* Setup the settings you want


[New Repo screenshot](/static/images/unc/bacs350/git-new-repo.png)

[Repo Settings screenshot](/static/images/unc/bacs350/git-repo-settings.png)


### Clone your repo onto your computer
* Clone Your repository
* Setup Windows file location - Recommend "Documents/BACS350"

[Github Desktop screenshot](/static/images/unc/bacs350/git-Github-Desktop.png)

[Clone Repo screenshot](/static/images/unc/bacs350/git-changes.png)


### Add your existing code
* You have already created code for this class
* Move the desired code into your new directory
* Create file structure in your repository
    * bacs350
        * .git
            * config
            * objects ... lots of files
        * index.php
        * ReadMe.md
        * images
        * project
            * 01
            * 02
            * 03
        * skills
        * superhero
            * index.php
            * views.php
            * style.css
* NOTE: You do not want to transfer the .git directory to Bluehost
* Capture a screen shot

<img src="{{ skills }}/git-files.png" width="100%">

See [Instructor's Solution](https://unco-bacs.org/bacs350/skills/git-files.png) for an example


### Commit Changes
* From Start Menu launch Github Desktop
* Pin to taskbar
* View the changes to your files
* Capture a screen shot of your pending changes
* Commit the changes with a commit message
* Push the code back to the Github server

**Example**

[Show me a screenshot](/static/images/unc/bacs350/git-changes.png)

**My Changes before Commit**

<img src="{{ skills }}/git-changes.png" width="100%">

See [Instructor's Solution](https://unco-bacs.org/bacs350/skills/git-changes.png) for an example

**Push Changes to Server**

[Push Repo screenshot](/static/images/unc/bacs350/git-push.png)


